laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is poorly defined with extensive surrounding fat stranding and several locules of extraluminal gas. Findings are compatible with perforated appendicitis with contained perforation. A small adjacent collection contains an air-fluid level possibly representing an abscess measuring approximately 2.4 x 4.0 cm. Marked thickening of the cecal base.
Borderline serum creatinine; reported value was 2.0 mg/dL.
